Released version 0.9.1 with guidance template test fixes
## Summary
Fixed 8 failing tests in `test_guidance_builder.py` that were checking for content that changed when the guidance templates were rewritten. Successfully released version 0.9.1.

## Changes Made
- Updated assertions in `test_detailed_has_behavioral_examples` to accept "CORRECT behavior" or "**CORRECT**"
- Updated `test_templates_have_namespaces` to check for "decision/learned/blocker" instead of "decisions/learnings/blockers"
- Updated `test_build_minimal` to accept "MANDATORY" or "RULE" instead of "REQUIRED"
- Updated `test_build_standard` to accept "RULE 1" or "Rule 1" (case flexible)
- Updated `test_build_detailed` to accept "CORRECT/WRONG" and check for "ACCOUNTABILITY" or "FAILURE" sections
- Updated token estimation tests with increased limits (500/1500/2500 vs 250/1000/1700)

## Related Files
- tests/test_guidance_builder.py:70-132 (test assertions updated)
- tests/test_guidance_builder.py:198-227 (token estimation tests)

